==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Roe, Richard
<hw>Roe, Richard</hw>. <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A fictious name for a
party, real or fictious, to an act or proceeding. Other names were
formerly similarly used, as <altname>John-a-Nokes</altname>, <xex>John
o'</xex>, or <xex>of the</xex>, <xex>Nokes</xex>, or <xex>Noakes</xex>,
<altname>John-a-Stiles</altname>, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Roed</ent>⟦br⟧
